// ─── QUICK START CHECKLIST ───────────────────────────────────────
// 1. Create DB10 "ModbusData" (non-optimized) with the structure above
// 2. Add MB_SERVER call in OB1, pointing MB_HOLD_REG to DB10
// 3. Configure Technology Object "Axis_1" for your servo drive
//    - PTO mode: Use S7-1200 high-speed outputs (Q0.0, Q0.1)
//    - PROFINET: If SGD7S has PROFINET option module
// 4. In CPU Properties → Protection: Enable "Permit access with PUT/GET"
// 5. Connect the hardware using a D-Link DES-1008C switch:
//    - Port 1: Connected to the Node.js Host PC
//    - Port 2: Connected to the Siemens S7-1200 PLC
//    - Port 3: Connected to the MP2300S Motion Controller
//    Note: Since the S7-1200 has only a single physical Ethernet port, the switch is required to bridge the network.
// 6. Download to PLC, set CPU to RUN
// 7. Start Node.js backend: cd backend && node server.js
// 8. Open web dashboard → Login → Axis Control → Servo ON → Jog FWD!
